         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden, ¶ 26. June 62 ¶ My dear Professor. ¶  ¶ I am truly obliged for your very kind attention to my letter, but sympathize deeply with the loss you have sustained in your family. ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.06.26g</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Trans. 15.7.94. To proof. Bot. names checked by Jim Ross 1/99.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black edged.</p>
               </note>Melbourne botan. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26. June 62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Professor.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am truly obliged for your very kind attention to my letter, but sympathize deeply with the loss you have sustained in your family.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">HC: who has died - his mother, wife? Not one of the botanists.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> May providence retain for you long all the other members of your family and may your promising son transfer the celebrated name of D.C. to future generations.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am much pleased to learn, that the Ionidium Vernonii proves a distinct species. It is far less frequent than the I. filiforme.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the 8/<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">April</hi>
               </seg> I have already pr. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Suffolk</hi>
               </seg> forwarded in a case adressed to Dr Sonder (with other things) for you a copy of the first vol. of "the plants indigenous to Victoria."<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B 62.03.03.</p>
               </note> This volume should reach you some time in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">July</hi>
               </seg>; and should it not arrive perhaps you will kindly enquire about it at our friend Dr Sonder, to whom I have sent all the continental donation-copies for distribution, otherwise this work as well as the fragmenta are available at Wailhieus<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check spelling.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> establishments.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will afford me much pleasure to send you of Euphorbiaceae, Urticeae, Piperaceae, Cycadeae, Coniferae, Cupuliferae, Laurineae Wegoniaceae<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">J.Ross: </seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">
                        <hi rend="underline">B</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">egoniaceae?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I have not yet found indigenous to Australia &amp;c<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">delete the 'c'?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> as complete a set of specimens as is available at my herbarium for distribution. I shall be much engaged for a week, but then can readily send them &amp; will do this through Pamplins mediation.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check the early part of this paragraph - Rod says the sense suggests something wrong.</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>HC: it reads to me as though he will send the specimens via Pamplin,</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I can be of utility to any of the scientific institutions of Geneve by sending zoological, botanical or oryctognosy or geolog. specimens, or geographical maps or ethnolog. specimens or any information I may have within my reach I will be happy to place my services at your command.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With sentiments of the highest veneration &amp; regard, dear Professor, yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mons. le Professeur Alph. de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="4"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="4"/>&amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Genève.</p>
         </div>
